                            <h2>Causes of indigestion</h2>
                            <p>There are many possible causesTrusted Source of indigestion. These can range from dietary and lifestyle habits to the side effects of medications and serious underlying conditions.<br><br></p>
                            <h3>Lifestyle</h3>  
                            <p>result of eating a lot or eating too fast.<br><br>

                                Spicy, greasy, and fatty foods also increase the riskTrusted Source of indigestion. Lying down too soon after eating can make it harder to digest food. This increases your risk of abdominal discomfort. <br><br>
                                
                                Other common causes of poor digestion include:<br><br></p>
                            <ul class="ul">
                                    <li><a href="">smoking</a></li>
                                    <li>drinking too much <a href="">alcohol</a></li>
                                    <li><a href="">stress</a></li>
                                </ul>
                                <h3>Medication</h3>
                                <p>Indigestion can be a side effectTrusted Source of taking specific medications. <br><br>

                                    Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs, such as aspirin, ibuprofen, and naproxen, are one class of medications that can cause indigestion.<br><br>
                                    
                                    Antibiotics, medications that treat or prevent bacterial infections, can also irritate the digestive system and cause indigestion as a side effect.<br><br></p>
                                <h3>Medical conditions</h3>
                                <p>Several medical conditions can also <a href="">causes</a>Trusted Source indigestion. These include:</p>
                                <ul class="ul">
                                    <li><a href="">gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)</a></li>
                                    <li> <a href="">gastric cancer</a></li>
                                    <li>pancreatic or bile duct abnormalities</li>
                                    <li><a href="">peptic ulcers</a></li>
                                    <li><a href="">lactose, gluten</a>, and other intolerances</li>
                                    <li><a href="">irritable bowel syndrome (IBS)</a></li>
                                    <li><a href="">gastroparesis</a></li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>Sometimes you may experience indigestion with no apparent cause. The medical term for this is functional dyspepsia.

